#Text=Natalie Cressman
#Text=Natalie
#Text=Cressman
#Text=is an American jazz trombonist and vocalist .
#Text=Early life
#Text=Cressman was born in San Francisco to Sandy and Jeff Cressman who are jazz musicians as well .
#Text=Growing up in the San Francisco Bay Area , she began to play her first gigs in her early teens with various Jazz , Afro-Cuban , and Brazilian Jazz groups .
#Text=Her influences include Elis Regina , Joni Mitchell , Paul Simon , Herbie Hancock and Weather Report .
#Text=When Natalie turned 18 she moved to New York to study at Manhattan School of Music on scholarship , where she studied with Luis Bonilla , Garry Dial , Laurie Frink , and Wycliffe Gordon .
#Text=In her first semester , she was asked to join Phish guitarist Trey Anastasio 's solo project , and has been touring with TAB ever since .

#Text=Now based in Brooklyn , she is involved in various projects , including longtime mentor Peter Apfelbaum 's new project S P A R K L E R. She has released 2 albums in her own right , both self-produced , Unfolding and Turn the Sea , which feature primarily her own compositions .
#Text=Her original music is a blend of singer/songwriter , jazz , funk , and world music . [ 1 ]
#Text=Performances
#Text=In her junior year of high school , she performed at the Monterey and North Sea Jazz Festivals with the Next Generation Orchestra .

#Text=In 2008-9 , she was selected to perform in several youth honor bands , including the Jazz Band of America , California All State Jazz Band , Jazz Band Classic , and the Grammy Jazz Ensemble . [ 2 ]
#Text=Since moving to New York she has performed with Nichoas Payton 's Television Symphony Orchestra and Peter Apfelbaum 's New York Hieroglyphics Ensemble .
#Text=In May 2012 she played the Apollo Theater as a soloist in Wycliffe Gordon 's Jazz A La Carte , which also featured renowned performers Savion Glover and Maurice Hines .
#Text=She founded her own band called the Secret Garden , and released her first recording Unfolding , a modern jazz album with some world music and folk influences . [ 3 ]
#Text=She has also appeared with such groups as Van Ghost , Dumpstaphunk , and Lettuce , and has spent several years as an Artist at Large at Bear Creek Music Festival . [ 4 ]
#Text=Recordings
#Text=She recorded her first album with Secret Garden , titled " Unfolding " , in October 2011 at North 6th Media Labs , which was released on her family 's label , Cressman Music in late 2012 .
#Text=She followed her debut up with a second album , Turn the Sea , released on March 11 , 2014 under her own name .
#Text=The sophomore release continues her exploration of cross-pollinating jazz with more modern musical styles , resulting in a sound unique to her .
#Text=Cressman followed up in 2016 with the release of Etchings in Amber with guitarist Mike Bono .
#Text=The two traveled the country in October and November 2016 in support of the album .
#Text=On March 3 , 2017 , her latest release , Traces , melds a sleek and sensuous electronica-laced sound with a trace or two of dance floor sweat .
#Text=The new 5-song EP , which also includes Bono on the guitar tracks , can be heard on soundcloud https://soundcloud.com/natcressman/sets/the-traces-ep [ 5 ]
